<br>
Argggh i hate this !!!! Cant you just experiment and find out? <br>
<br>
It's not like i am trying to be the big end all and know it all, but there are so many different ways you 'can' use as an alternate pulling method.<br>
<br>
Some may save you getting beat on, some may save you time giveing you a few extra seconds to get distance from the mob.<br>
<br>
And some can be used to gain you extra time to land a snare on a mob, or a fear or a whatever.<br>
<br>
<br>
Ok here is one example:<br>
You cast a spell to pull the orc pawn, and an orc centurian attacks as well, you run down a corridor and Feign death.<br>
the two orcs stand there a second and one of them starts walking off and is not back at it's spawn point... so it means if you stand both have a good chance of agroing you.<br>
while you are feigned you type /pet attack and the pet charges the orc pawn..... thankfully the orc is far enough not to attack, your pet dies and the centurian is back at it's spawn point, you can now stand and agro the pawn and take it back to group.<br>
     This is basicaly what i call pet tagging, if you have no one else who can realaistically tag - it's not used every day but it can be used in certain circumstances like Splitting lower velks kobolds who basically path back at the exact same speed. (handy if you cant land a snare because of lv)<br>
<br>
You can snare a mob, sent pet into attack and fear it, then use an agro spell to pull a second mob... a few mobs chase your pet down until the pet stops to melee....... while you run your mob out of range, by the time you pet dies you have your mob out of agro range and hence solo pull.......... there are other ways to do this, you can use fear/snare to out distance mobs but in some circumstances neither of these are an option, you may also simple want a few seconds to run out of spell range etc or just get range to feign more cleanly.<br>
<br>
you can use a pet to avoid line of sight, and my fav is you use a pet to attack somethig not in line of sight, then run back to an advantage point, pet dies - you cast invis then run back to the group - because you are invis only the mobs that attacked your pet will agro, anythhing that cannot see you while invis will not attack, you can do this other ways for instance - in droga when i wanted to break the Rukgus spawn at an low lv, i would snare a mob, fear it, invis then run a few rooms down.. when the fear broke i would lure the mob to the room i was in so i did not have addds....... i also used that to pull the spawns one by one out of a room so that the 5 healers would not chain heal it.<br>
<br>
Useing a pet on big mobs to gain distance is particulary usefull, as you can send a pet in then run back.......... usefull for say Zelnithack for beginers, what you do is summon a pet, send it to attack the creature then cast Invis before pet reaches melee, invis is a few second - can use the bloodember bracers for 10 second cast but that is tricker imho - then pet agros, pet dies zelnithack charges you... by that time your invis just landed so you can run back to group bringing just the one creature in... nothing else will agro because you are invis and cant see you (except for a few undead and shaman with see invis at odd times) <br>
<br>
You can use pets in many ways, both useing it to avoid line of sight, distance, spell range, fear tactics, meat shield and even use it to absorb a spell or two.... casters NPC like necros love to open with slow spells, useing a pet to pull hard necro mobs can be extreemly powerful as it can buy you a very long time, enough time to fear the necro's pet snare him invis and lure back to group single with no agro.<br>
<br>
Yes there are even more trivial methods i did not go into - these were just a few, and yes there are often better methods and people willing to help you on the pull........but in some circumstances you may not want people with you on the pull etc... luckily i am lucky enough to have a very dedicated guild monk and good bunch of clerics who res my ass, and a good few SK's waiting for there chance to participate.<br>
<br>
Do i use these things here all the time? no i dont, but if i think useing a pet will save a life, or allow me to move the mob to a better place so that somone can tag off me....... sure i will do it.<br>
<br>
I can pull the Va`Dyn single to the zoneline, sure i need one person to assist on the pull, Ixihunxi assists me on the pull and she is a shaman. Yet we Get the Vah`Dyn to the zoneline single....when we get an add it's usualy corridor wandering mobs.<br>
<br>
I think only once now that we know how to pull him, have we ever got an add, and that was because my feign failed due to an extreem bug, instead of dieng and trying again i decided to recover the pull - we got one add, and the Vah`Dyn.. wich wasnt so bad.<br>
<br>
SO by all means, please feel that you can flame these week tactics with pets - they are not perfect but can be used when 'normal' methods do not work, me i just have a lot of tricks up my sleeve and well, i do die a lot, but that is because god forbit i do pulls that 80% of the sk's on this server would not dare do.<br>
