It's actually a nice change, for once i can be happy to pull with a pet summoned.. i do often anyway, i like to have my pet around believe it or not.. appart from its obviouse benifits it's fun to do a bit of melee, casting and controlling a pet.<br>
     I always use the old type commands for a pet, the pet window is almost useless to me and hotkeys are useless (except /pet back off).<br>
If you cast a spell (say 4 second spell) you cant click any hotkeys, so cant mash the /pet attack hotkey or pet controll buttons.... But you can type &quot;/pet attack&quot; into the chat window and do it that way..... <br>
     So what i often do is pull a mob, run back to camp and stop - beging to cast dooming darkness &amp; type &quot;/pet attack&quot; the pet engages the mob and takes a round or two of melee.. mean while my dooming darkness is 80% the way through it's channeling and lands on the mob causeing it to run towards me.<br>
<br>
The reason i do that is snare a mob while it is not in melee and it will break early (druid dot patch) because our snare is a dot.. and hence does 75% if the target is not in melee range, again this is dead simple to test.<br>
So i let pet engage in melee, while darnkess hits a second early - back up and cast fear... that way my first darkness lasts the full duration not 75%.<br>
